# Turn on the rewrite engine
RewriteEngine On

# Remove .html extension from files
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME}.html -f
RewriteRule ^(.*)$ $1.html [L]


### How to Implement This:

**Step 1: Upload the `.htaccess` File**

Place the new `.htaccess` file in your `public_html` directory on Hostinger. It should be in the same folder as your `index.html`, `about.html`, etc.

**Step 2: Update All Your HTML Links**

You now need to go through all your HTML files (`index.html`, `services.html`, `portfolio.html`, `about.html`, and `contact.html`) and remove the `.html` extension from every link in the navigation and footer.

For example, in your `header`, you will change this:

```html
<!-- OLD LINKS -->
<ul class="nav-links">
    <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="services.html">Services</a></li>
    <li><a href="portfolio.html">Portfolio</a></li>
    <li><a href="about.html">About Us</a></li>
    <li><a href="contact.html">Contact</a></li>
</ul>